The paper proposes a system for assisting users in creating 3D models through the use of recorded and analyzed workflows. This involves the use of brushing interfaces and data-driven and procedural modeling techniques. Given the focus on 3D modeling and user interaction, the most likely category is cs.GR (Graphics). However, the use of machine learning and data-driven techniques suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible categories. The focus on user interaction and workflow analysis suggests that cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possible category. Finally, the use of machine learning and data-driven techniques also suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category.
